Nairobi county executives will be fired after one year if they don’t perform, Governor Mike Sonko has said.  Sonko yesterday said the contracts of all executives will be renewed after every year. “Non-performing members will automatically go home regardless of whom they are or where they come from,” Sonko said. His cabinet include Hitan Majevdia (Health), Allan Igambi (Trade), Janet Ouko (Education), Mohamed Dagane (Transport), Charles Kerich (Lands), Peter Njuguna (Agriculture) and Emmah Mukuhi (ICT). Read: No one safe in anti-graft war, Sonko warns his cabinet Click here for the latest political news